      "role": "user",
      "content": "it just feels like a coping mechanism tho. like, talking about \"ripples of positivity\" feels so small and even delusional when you look at the actual data. it's not just a bad phase, it's a systemic collapse. it feels like we're being told to keep decorating our rooms while the house is actively burning down. how can anyone actually find meaning in that? it feels fundamentally irrational to keep trying.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
